<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="498" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d498">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/523.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minster to
                                    Haiti</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The instructions of your March 8 were informally presented to the Haitian
                            Government today, and I am assured that Haiti will continue to do
                            everything possible to maintain neutrality.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Furniss</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-11">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 11, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The two Rodriguez and Horacio Vásquez, en route to Cuba, arrived here
                                today on the French steamer. The Haitian Government refused to allow
                                them to land.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Furniss.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>